caption: The behavior of the staff was really rude. The chicken wings tasted sweet, even after asking for spicy ones.
We were amazed for those ramen. They are doing an excellent job with the food they serve. Recommend

Amazing! My GF and I went here a couple years back and to check it out and were amazed by how intimate and cozy the restaurant is. The Takoyaki and the Spicy Ramen are beyond words as well as their sake. The whole visit was affordable, delicious, and most importantly deserving of many MANY repeat visits. Thank you Friends Ramen team, you are making memories.
Me and my girls love this place!!! So happy we can dine in again!

The gimmick is a nice touch to the traditional huge bowl of ramen. Instead Friends Ramen offers smaller bowls that way you can try more than one flavor ramen because they do have a lot more options that your typical ramen spot.They also have these little card hanging everywhere as soon as you walk in. Visitors can write something nice on there and hang it up, very cute. If it weren't for the small bowl alternative Im not sure I would keep coming back to this spot. The overall flavor of the ramen is just okay but definitely not packed full of flavor like you would get elsewhere. A cute little spot none the less if youre looking to try multiple flavors or are just looking for a lighter meal.  Also if you like sushi, Friends Sushi is right next door and it is sooo good.
Once I tried it, I kept going back. It definitely every month
This spot is wonderful and roomy, the menu was delicious and the rates were very inexpensive. fast, productive service and very amiable staff. Recommended.

Great ramen and great food. During these times where take out is the only option, they took exceedingly long even after I arrived to pick up the food well after it said it would be completed. There was no apology and somehow the ramen was cold along with the rice with an almost non existen amount of pork sauce when I actually requested extra. I can't believe how disapointing this experience was.
The ramen is delicious, and the interior decor is very asthetically pleasing.
Small portions

My fiance and I LOVE Friends sushi and today I was in the area so I stopped by to try Friends Ramen... I was not disappointed!! even just for takeout the Chicken Karaage Ramen was amazing. So good! I also got my food and was in and out very quickly!

Coming back to this review a year later to say this is my favorite restaurant in Chicago! My boyfriend and I have been coming here since we started dating because we can always count on great food and fun music. Also, Moses is the best! Big thumbs up!

Ramen and the atmosphere at this location is super good. Stopped in on a Monday I think. I've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting. This place has a nice feel to it. Feels similar to a cafe in Chicago I liked.
The small is small, the large is sharable, but the food is very tasty
Its good. Especially the buns and the Ramen.
Support delicious small businesses! Which this place has an abundance for: delicious ramen and other food. But go for ramen!
Great Ramen and some great service!

I sent my friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are yummy and the stuff is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we go to this place we pass a splendid evening.  warmly recommended.
This place is always the best, I can't really remember a time I could say something was wrong with my food. Truly amazing place for all the Japanese food lovers. Their rice bowls are the bomb
Poor value for the price, and poor noodles - not an authentic 面. Descent Vegetable broth with the Niku-Ramen.
A top scene for tasty Ramen. Great place to chill, get away, eat some good food. The service here is great.
Delicious ramen and appetizers. Cute space that feels very authentic.

The food is awful. There’s nothing Japanese about it. $1 instant ramen tastes more authentic than whatever we were served. The gyozas had sour taste to them, which makes me think they were on the verge of being spoiled. “Ramen” was served in a disposable black plastic bowl. The contents of the bowl were: questionable looking white  liquid, semi-cold spaghetti noodles, and for 2 variations of ramen that we got, one came with chicken nuggets from Costco and the other one with something that used to be a pork belly a week ago. All with the price tag of $65. To be fair we did have 2 bottles of sake, but even those didn’t make the food taste less terrible Service was nice.

Really nice people, terrible food.  Think Tyson nuggets and spaghetti-ish noodles in a disposable plastic bowl for the tonkotsu ramen.  Hard to even call it ramen.  Wish I could say better since the staff was nice, but we got burned.
Seafood ramen really good. Also the black milk tea.

(Translated by Google) Rather disappointed with this restaurant. I called before going and was told the kitchen closes at 8:45 am. I arrived at 8:30 am and the waiter pressed us to order before he even offered to sit down. So we order, in the end not that cheap, the ramen has $ 17 without tax and tips. We sit down, finally the waiter brings us our dishes in plastic bowls and cups. We quietly watch TV with the NBA game and he turns off the TV. We ask if he can put it back on until we finish eating and he says no because otherwise "we risk never leaving". I thought it was a joke and actually not at all. Next time if they really want to shut down, don't accept us.  Quite disappointed by this restaurant. Not so cheap ($ 17 for a Ramen before tax and tips) and obvious that the server only waited for us to leave (arrived at 8:30 pm whereas restaurant opens until 10pm). Won't come again.  (Original) Plutôt déçue de ce restaurant. J'ai appelé avant d'y aller et on me dit que la cuisine ferme à 8h45. J'arrive à 8h30 et le serveur nous presse pour commander avant même qu'il nous propose d'êtres assis. Donc on commande, au final pas si cheap que ça, le ramen a $17 sans tax et tips. On s'assoit, finalement le serveur nous apporte nos plats dans des bols et cups en plastiques. On regarde tranquillement la TV avec le match de NBA et la il coupe la TV. On demande s'il peut la remettre le temps qu'on finisse de manger et il dit non car sinon "on risque de ne jamais partir". Je pensais que c'était une blague et en fait pas du tout. La prochaine fois si ils veulent vraiment fermer, qu'ils ne nous acceptent pas.  Quite disappointed by this restaurant. Not so cheap ($17 for a Ramen before tax and tips) and obvious that the serveur only waited for us to leave (arrived at 8h30pm whereas restaurant opens until 10pm). Won't come again.
Not impressed at all. Just a ok ramen
One of my go-to spots to grab some food. very good location, always clean, and awesome customer service. Highly recommended!
Its okay, nothing to write home about.   My teen  loved the chicken dumplings.

I just don't like the taste. It's not authentic as I hope. The spicy shrimp is not spicy at all. The broth is the same for the spicy shrimp and spicy miso ramen. The customer service is great, and it was super fast.

I take my family to this lovely place from time to time! This is my favorite place to have a bite.  I visit this place routinely. The cooking is excellent, the staff members are welcoming and the charge is decent. I enjoy meeting in this spot over a good meal.
Great customer service! Had the beef & rice bowl. Was fantastic, it was worth every penny. I'll definitely come back.
This is a great restaurant it has amazing chicken Ramen and has even better staff and service
The best RAMEN in ILLINOIS. This place will blow your mind.
Cool ramen

No complaints about the food! It's fast, delicious, and reasonably priced (especially for the area). The staff is attentative and friendly. My only complaint is the loud music, which is a mix between EDM, trap, and house music. I find this to be an odd music choice at 1 in the afternoon, but that might just be me. Pro Tip: the seats are pretty small if you're a large (6 foot+) person, so just be aware.
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I like how the service is always great and they keep the place well kept at all times. Pricing is fair and they serve big portions.

This is no doubt one of the most pleasant place to eat in the region. Anytime I come to this place I am very glad. They always keep their high  standard service and the highest level of dishes  they give. You are always happy with this place. Highly  recommended.

First time in Chicago and this was an excellent pick.  Why order one big bowl of ramen when I can go for a smaller portion but with more superb dishes.  The small was a bit small but when I paired with 3 other dishes, it was enough for 2.  It came out to be $20/per person with a bottle of delicious sake to share.  We got the ebi katsu, spicy miso ramen, pork belly salad and another fried shrimp appetizer.

Staff couldn’t be friendlier and the food couldn’t be better! Intimate setting with great music and such a cozy environment. Couldn’t ask for a better spot for an evening meal and hot tea on a cold winter day!!

This place is in the running for my favorite ramen place in Chicago. Awesome Tokyo vibes inside. Significantly more vegetarian ramen/steamed bun options than other ramen places. I like how they do small servings (6-8 dollars a bowl) which allows you to try different flavors. You can also get a full size bowl if wanted. They serve drinks, good selections of Japanese beverages. Will definitely be coming back.
Slammin'

Unique in the area. Prices are top notch compared with theirs. Atmosphere has a sense of authenticity. Ordered an okonomiyaki and a spicy miso ramen.. Small ramen for $6 IS really small.. The broth was a surprise...Rich in flavor and   with the right balance of texture... The noodle is very fresh but not the typical ramen you might have eaten before. With one piece of pork n a quarter of an egg...It's decent.  The okonomiyaki... However was little bit letdown...It's not really authentic at all..It's basically like a larger version of takoyaki without the octopus.. Mostly cabbage and batter... Flavor was one dimension with all the Kewpie mayonnaise... Still kept with bonito flakes and nori flakes... Not so special and relatively small...For $9..  It's alright for lunch or on the go... Service was fast.. Just won't go that often.. Three stars for the effort.....

I loved the food and the intimate setting. The seating area is pretty small and can probably only accommodate around 20-25 people. The food was wonderful. I had the Chicken Ramen and the Garden Salad. There was also an interesting wall where people had hung little pieces of paper that looked liked wishes. (See my picture.)

This is a very small restaurant so if you don't want to wait inline get there before 6 pm. We ordered two combos one with chicken ramen, chicken gyoza and salad and the other one with Veggie Spicy Miso Ramen, Vegetable gyoza and salad. I recommend getting the combo if you don't want just the ramen, if you do want just the ramen, I would ask for a large bowl, the small one is not enough if you will only eat ramen. You can also order 2-3 smaller ones with different flavors and try a couple of the many options that they offer.  Chicken Ramen egg noodle, vegetable soup, steamed chicken, scallion, kale, ginger, bamboo topped with fried shallot  Chicken Gyoza Deep-fried chicken dumpling with house sauce  Veggie Spicy Miso Ramen rice noodle, vegetable soup, corn, bamboo, tofu, scallion, fungus, shichimi togarashi, miso & chili paste  Vegetable Gyoza Deep-fried veggies dumping serve with house sauce  House salad spring mix, lettuce, carrot, corn, tomato with wasabi ginger dressing

I call this superb restaurant every couple of days  as I love the good air that is part of this restaurant. The staff is awfuly cordial and skilfull. The service is deeply efficient. Needless to say, the food they serve is magnificent. I ate there many times and I was always pleased. The pay is decent. I suggest this place to all my friends.
Best food, super nice employees, always excellent mood. They charge affordable pricing and the food quality is very good. Keep up the good work.
This is a go to spot for me. Consistently good ramen and I love that you can get the small bowls. Quick service and I love the decor. I’m a big fan of the kimchi ramen!

This tiny authentic place has the best menu because you can try MANY things. Most ramen places bring you a bowl larger than your face, but here at Friends ramen, you can order small sizes and try several different flavors for a great price.
This spot offers excellent service as well as enjoyable meals. One of the best place in town. The food came out fast and the rates were reasonable. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.

I come to this excellent place every couple of days since I love the ambiance that is outline this restaurant. The personel is exceptionally cordial and experienced. The service is remarkablywonderfully rapid. Not to mention, the food they prepare is good. I have been there more than once and I was always happy. The price is reasobable. I recommend this restaurant to all my friends.
Good food and service.

This is doubtless one of the most pleasant place to eat in the region. Anytime I go there I am incredibly satisfied. They maintain their high  level service and the topmost level of cooking  they provide. You can never go wrong with this place. Highly  recommended.
Fun atmosphere and good food
Delicious ramen. My girlfriend and I like to order a variety of small bowls, two sides, and warm sake. That makes for a low-key night. That tan tan men ramen is fire tho!!

Literally our favorite ramen place in the entire Chicago area. From the fun decor to the hip hop soundtrack, this place's food and prices can't be beat! Do a Jello Sake shot for me while you're there.

Friends is an OK hipster ramen place. Their food is rather bland for ramen and will not be spicy if advertised. Their noodles taste like they came directly from a pasta box. The meat quality is below average and the broth is also pretty lacking in flavor. The price is very fair per portion size and they do have option for small portions. The service is friendly and quick as well.

Very tasty. Would recommend they change the BIG sign outside the store front that says “ALL RAMEN 6 DOLLARS”  As none of the ramens are 6 dollars and they range from $6.50- $15.50  After tip expect to pay 8 dollars for a dollop if very tasty ramen.
This is chinese ramen.

I go with my wife to this great spot often! This is the best place to dine.  I visit this place regularly. The food is excellent, the team is friendly and the prices are reasonable. I enjoy meeting in this restaurant to have a good dinner.
The food was great and the staff was very nice, but the portions could definitely be bigger. So unfortunately I'd have to give 3 stars due to small portions.
Moses is the best

Authentic - super delicious - very healthy and very well presented food. The only downside is that the place is a bit cramped up. Hardly any place to wait up or even move around. Though the interiors are beautiful.
Was fantastic! Definitely a gem in the city!
The spot is awesome and broad, the meals was delightful and the prices were very fair. rapidly, productive service and very welcoming staff members. I recommend this place.
Great food. I had the karaage with rice, ebi katsu and crispy shrimp. Loved all of them. Very flavorful food.  Friendly and helpful server.
Delicious!! And normal portion sizes.. I love ramen but the portions are usually too big. The sizes here are perfect and leaves you with room for appetizer or dessert

I shy away from giving it too good a review because I want to eat here again and I don't  want to wait too long.  I like the rustic and quirky atmosphere as a respite from the hustle of the Chicago downtown.  Great alternative for something  unexpectedly  different  for date night but probably  not so good for large groups.
Awesome food, very kind staff, always great mood. They charge affordable rates and the food quality is awesome. Highly recommended.
Absolutely amazing ramen, amazing ambiance, and super friendly staff. This is honestly one of the best ramen places in the city. Highly recommend a visit!
we ordered spicy miso and regular miso ramens,  they were  not bad, but the miso taste needs to be stronger, it's a little water down.
Good price for ramen ! I would go again , tasted good and was satisfying as well.

What a wonderful little place! It is haunted by the spirit of good foods and warm, friendly faces. She grants wishes, which you can read the ones she granted on the wall when you walk in! The little ramen bowls are so good, the noodles are so soft, it's almost as if it is magic
Good ramen in St chicago
Best Ramen place in downtown Chicago! My boy Zac & I had a badass lunch break here. Highly recommend it to anyone needing a delicious bite to eat.
The bowl is very small, even I bought a large size for 15$, there are not many noodles in it. Most importantly, the kitchen and restroom is not clean. Disappointed. Won’t go again.
Great little ramen bowls

Absolutely delicious! Very friendly for a college budget considering the area it is in. The interior is super aesthetic. I've gone to way more expensive Ramen places and have had so much worse. The small bowls let you try different things. Go with someone you're comfortable sharing food with and order 4 or 5 small bowls! You can feast if you want to or keep it cheap. It's all up to you but, regardless of what you do, it's gonna be delicious.
Good spot for warm sake 🙃
(Translated by Google) Excellent site! High quality food, excellent service, highly recommended!  (Original) Excelente sitio!! Comida de gran calidad, excelente servicio, ampliamente recomendable!
Delicious.  So many chouces
That little bowl of seafood ramen really hit the spot.  Didn't wait long for my food. It was perfect.
Absolutley delish!
The easiest and fastest 5 star rating I've ever given a restaurant. I recommend the tan tan man. Music could have been a bit quieter and fit the mood better though.
Good stop for ramen in a city asian atmosphere
Good service, nice ambient, o.k. food, a bit pricey.

The taste of the food was okay - I had the chicken karrage rice (large). The bowl was huge, but was 90% rice, so I basically overpaid for rice. The portions here are a little strange - $6 gets you a tiny bowl (basically a cup) of the dish or pay $15 for a large bowl (which is way too big for a normal person portion). So I'm not too keen on the pricing (it's a little on the high end, even for downtown ramen/rice). I probably would give this place a second chance, but stick with the small cup. Overall, a little disappointing considering the cost factor where there are other choices nearby
Such a great bowl of ramen.  Love this place.  You can ask for any level of spice though it seems like the dishes are pre set levels.  Just ask and it'll be adjusted to your preference

Worst ramen ever. This place is dark, smells bad and uncleaned, which made me feel uncomfortable at the first place. The food is just, like, rubbish. It is not ramen, they use spaghetti for noodle! The small bowl is tiny, like really tiny but the price is 6 dollar, so ridiculous.. Please do not go there, bad experience.
The seating/decor is unique and cozy and the prices are incredibly affordable. Food is great
Reasonable prices and decent food
Cute place. For $13 we had a light meal for 2.
Great ramen, I like the fact that they now have a large bowl option. However i find the seating extremely uncomfortable.

(Translated by Google) This is a Japanese restaurant run by a Thai.  I ordered only fried shrimp, fried dumplings, fried takoyaki, shrimp noodles, fried kale and fried food. I didn't realize that it was fried, because I didn't write anything about fried dumplings, takoyaki and kale. The taste of the sauce is a bit sweet.  Pork belly and dandan noodles are also different from Japanese flavors! However, this is good because it was delicious. The atmosphere of the store clerk was good, and I could eat various things little by little and have a pleasant meal.  (Original) こちらはタイ人経営の日本料理店。  小エビの唐揚げ、揚げ餃子、揚げたこ焼き、エビ練り天、フライドケールと揚げ物ばかり注文してしまいました。 餃子もたこ焼きもケールも揚げてるとは一言も書いてなかったので揚げ物だとは気付かず。 ソースの味などは少し甘いです。  豚バラ丼、担々麺も日本の味とは違う！ とはいえ、これはこれで美味しかったので良いかな。 店員さんの雰囲気も良かったし、少しずつ色々なものを食べれて楽しい食事が出来ました。
OK ramen place. Portions are really small. I guess they are meant to be tried for flavors. They don't have too many options for other Japanese food.
Great food
Fantastic ramen
Quick bus ride from my office to small ramen sampler bliss! Everything was great and the staff fast and friendly. Will definitely return...

(Translated by Google) A small raymen house located in the heart of the city. Unusually, it sells ramen and rice bowl in a small potion size. Strong adult men should eat about three bowls and feel full. The broth is thick but does not weave or feel. However, the surface was too similar to the udon noodles and tasteless. Rice bowls are neat and worth eating. It's hard to recommend it to ramen lovers, but it seems to be okay for a meal. The interior decor reminds me of Korea's Izakaya.  (Original) 시내 중심부에 위치한 자그마한 라멘집. 특이하게도 여기는 작은 포션 사이즈로 라멘이랑 덮밥을 판매한다. 건장한 성인남성은 세 그릇정도 먹어야지 포만감을 느낄 수 있다. 국물은 진하지만 짜거나 느끼하지는 않다. 하지만, 면이 너무 우동면과 비슷하고 맛이 없었다. 덮밥은 나름 깔끔하고 먹을만하다. 라멘애호가에게 추천하기는 어렵지만 끼니를 때우기 위해서는 괜찮은 것 같다. 내부 인테리어는 한국의 이자카야를 떠올리게 한다.
The food here was absolutely amazing, I got the fried shrimp appetizer and the seafood ramen - sooooo flavorful. The person serving was polite! I hate that you can’t get large servings to go

The portions are relatively small a for their price. It is a conveniently located restaurant, but the inside does smell very weird and not clean. Was an ok ramen shop to try once, but I would not go back.
It's LITERALLY the best ramen shop. The waitress tnat works the morning/afternoon shift on Fridays is the best. Oh my gosh I love the food
Great small bowl ramen
Really good ramen and fairly cheap for the middle of the city
The food is amazing! The only problem is the portion size and uncomfortable seating.
Very good ramen and good service!!!

Cool vibe. Got the veggie spicy ramen. It has chili oil in it to make it spicy but the broth got too oily. Noodles are plentiful, veggies on the lighter side. I’ve definitely had more flavorful ramen in other places but this place will do in a pinch.
I love the portion there and ofc, my fav is Kimchi Ramen and it's cheap there too
Ramen, yeah, awesome. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. The bill was fair I would say.
Embarrassingly poor seafood ramen! Wasted 15bucks for big bowl filled with overcooked mushy noodles with literally TWO tiny shrimps and couple of pieces of imitation crab meat! So awful!

This place is trash. As a first-time customer, I was unaware of the bowl sizes and corresponding prices. The menu lists all non-combo bowls as $6. I and the 3 other people who I was with were shocked and confused when each of our bills came out as $16?! When I asked the worker he defended himself by stating, "The menus are old. [False advertising much?!] I told you the price when you first sat down," which really explains why 4 people were dumbfounded by this discovery... No wonder they're still in business, they get by by scamming their customers. Even after being lied to, I wouldn't be upset if the food was worth it but sadly it wasn't. First and, needless to say, last time I'll be dining at Friends Ramen.

I have been coming to this restaurant every time I am in Chicago. The very first time I was at the restaurant, the staff explained the whole idea behind the small portion sizes: to try multiple different flavors of the ramen. However, now they have the big bowl which is a perfect size if you're already sure of which flavor you want! The decor and music is so aesthetically pleasing. They even play older animes on the TVs. The staff is sooooo nice and eager to build a good and lasting relationship with the customers. I have also never had a bad bowl of food here. The chicken karaage ramen is a MUST TRY! Definitely keep your mind open towards this small hole in the wall restaurant. Although the portion sizes are small and meant to be ordered in quantities of 2 or 3+ different flavors, the restaurant has amazing staff and charm that can't be passed up.
Great ramen and awesome atmosphere. The TV's in there are always playing videos of delicious Japanese food being cooked, which makes you even hungrier.

If I could only eat at 5 restaurants for rest of my life this would be one of them.  The food is fresh and its quality you can taste- you can't find something on the menu that is bad.  The service is fantastic, especially the guy who may or may not be running it.  Once we left our debit card there and he actually ran down the street with it to give it back to us. I mean C'MON no one does that in Chicago, expect for him.  Heads up the place is pretty tiny is and is not suited for large parties, there is only one table that would be able to accommodate a party of 5 or 6.
We tried almost the entire menu and it was outstanding. The customer service was nothing short of excellent as well. Best ramen I’ve had, definitely try the karaage ramen and the kimchi ramen
Delicious Ramen, and the small plates (bowls) style is great for trying everything on the menu
Cute ramen shop with tight seating but delicious ramen in these small cup bowls.
Good food and cool atmosphere, but after several bowls of food to make a meal it was spendy.
Cool little spot with a nice atmosphere and great music. Service was great. Love the $6 small bowls; it gives you an opportunity to try multiple bowls.
Best Ramen in the area, loved the small pan style serving of Ramen. Best place to grab a Ramen on the go. Service is excellent and the ambience is so good
Really small place but very warm and welcoming i love this ramen spot its not pricey and they have big or small bowls depending on the appetite. Love this place i go almost every week
Loved it! Great prices and I love the small bowls as I cannot eat much at a time. Delicious food, cozy atmosphere.

Delicious Ramen place with friendly staff, $15 for a giant bowl of ramen and wooden benches. They played great music, and the wait was not long at all. My Tan Tan Man was spicy and I coughed a little more than usual but by god did I finish it to the last drop and then left a couple of notes on the wishing wall. Delicious and extremely Hugh quality ramen with soft pork and delicious noodles. Highly recommend.

That was not ramen. We were craving a hot bowl of ramen on a cool day, but whatever they do, I will not call ramen. It is a novelty restaurant and that’s that. The reviews are SERIOUSLY misleading.  The service was good, music too loud, food very disappointing.

Really appreciated the small, affordable ramen bowls that allowed us to sample multiple tasty flavors and styles. Also liked that they had more than one vegetarian option and that they were clearly labeled in the menu. Finally, the service and staff was efficient and super friendly!

The ramen soup that I ordered was very delicious. However, there are a couple of things that I think should be improved: - background music was RnB style, not really matching the interior and the cuisine - if a restaurant/cafe claims to serve ramen (Asian noodle soup), it is unacceptable and disappointing to get spaghetti instead of Asian noodles, especially if they look as if they were bought in a supermarket - price for the regular bowl (proper meal) was 15$, which I think is quite expensive.
Incredible tasting ramen and fair prices. The chicken used in my order was so good I'm still thinking about it.
Weird atmosphere in a good way. Super chill Westernized-Asain vibe a la Seoul Taco. Cheap bowls ~ $6 each with a good quantity.

Great small spot to meet up with a friend or two. Prices are cheap but portions are small, so make sure to order an appetizer! Very friendly staff and laid back environment. Right off the Chicago Red Line easy one minute walk. I recommend checking it out.
Darling little ramen shop. Small bowls are perfect for lunch and reasonably priced. Vegetarian options galore as well as carnivorous options for meat eaters in the group.
Love it here.  Go everytime I'm in chicago

Small but cozy. If you want a quick snack, get the small ramen bowls but if you are hungry, definitely go for big bowl.  Not the very best ramen place but good option for that area and really not crazy expensive.  Would return if I have ramen cravings and just happened to be in that area.
Food was great, but the server charged me an extra $6 for two drinks they never brough
Take some friends and try them all. Great service and cold beer! Will be back soon
Good
Pretty good - got the $15 large bowl of spicy miso ramen

Food was good. Definitely bar style food and atmosphere with hip music and tapas style or bowl food. Tried the spicy miso ramen, chicken karaage ramen, takoyaki  and pork and rice bowl  ramen were good and takoyaki was ok. Pork bowl could've been better but it was for a child so it did its job. I ordered a Sapporo draft and while it went down smoothly but hoped there were more options. The first table we sat at had this wet mop stench and we ended up moving to a table with super heavy wooden chairs.  I recommend this place if you're out shopping on Mag Mile but I still would say go try Slurping Turtle or Ramen-san if you're craving more authentic ramen with plenty of broth to go around.
The space is very small and intimate and a few of the chairs were wobbly, but my waitress was happy to switch chairs for me. The portions are small but very filling and the karaage is delicious.
Great Ramen, but it's cold sometimes
Great date spot
Baby-sized portions. Charges $15 for a regular sized bowl.
Decent food, good price
Small portion is overpriced at $13, especially when you consider that the person who takes your order is a machine. Try Bibibop around the corner for better food and save $5
I'm here basically every week, and I can't stop coming back. Food is solid and a good price, the staff is so friendly and the decor is so welcoming and cute. Thanks for being you Friends!
Overpriced. Small portions. $6 appetizer smaller than my fingers. $15 big bowl ramen Valentines day special was decent size, but their normal bowls are a total ripoff.
Awesome ambiance. Played throwback hip hop, Mortal Kombat on one screen, amine on another, cozy dining area, and a ton of options for food. The spicy ramen is great.
Nice small place,$6 ramen bowls,I had 2

It's a great place for a couple or small group. The staff are helpful and friendly and the food is affordable and delicious. If you want an affordable, yet different place to eat I recommend F4iends Ramen
Intimate, cozy atmosphere. The food was delicious. Great service and affordable.
Excellent service,  phenomenal food, very flavorful dishes. Only gave 4 stars because it is a little cramped as it is a small location. They do make the most of their space.

Ramen was good and tasty. I wish they had larger portions/bowls.  I ordered three things from their menu and was full. My favorite was the potstickers and my ultimate favorite was their hot oil condiment!
Underground jem
Fantastic little place with great service and food. Can't wait to go back on our next trip to Chicago.

Excellent service. Scrumptious Spicy ramen and incredible decor it feels like you’ve been transported to a Japanese Resturant IN Japan. Intimate seating and you are provided with a tag on which you can write a prayer or wish or whatever and hang it, something I recall people do at Japanese temples. I throughly enjoyed my experience at this Ramon Resturant. Will return
Good ramen and nice cozy atmosphere. Portions are small - ramen comes in more of a cup than a bowl, but it's priced accordingly. Great service and Sapporo on tap
It's a great place to go for a nice bowl of ramen. Service is fast and food comes out quickly. They have to go and dine in. Almost never a wait time.
It's a great place. Except the seats. I don't fit in there.

Variety is the spice of life. Before going here I read a few reviews about portions being small, but I found they're inexpensive and the menu is designed to try more than one ramen or to get some other dishes. I liked it a lot since I don't eat a lot, but I do like variety. If you're a big eater, the price of 3 bowls is still less than a lot of ramen in the city. It's a tiny place, so service is quick to get you fed and on your way. Perfect place if you're craving ramen, but you like other dishes, or you want have more than one version. It's a pretty nice concept.
If you can get past the small dining room, it's a good place.  Friendly staff and good atmosphere.   Soup bowls are pricey for the amount you get though

Delicious food. I had the chicken ramen and I loved it. Every table has a bottle of their home made chilli oil which is very potent. Handle with care! The place is very small but love the ambiance and furniture. Portions are relatively small but well priced. What I like about that is that it allows you to try more options! Loved the place.
Small but delicious
This will be one of the shortest review I'll write.  This is - hands down - one of my favorite places to eat. Love the food, the people and the atmosphere. Eat here and be happy.
Great food and better music!
Good food, size is really small
Good ramen just small serving sizes especially considering the price, but that comes with the neighborhood. Atmosphere is cool and there is a good variety of choices for ramen.

Very cool spot with great atmosphere. Background music is hip hop which is a pretty cool and contrasting. Food is nice and comes in small bowls. Order 2-3 for a good size meal. Very friendly service too.

The BEST ramen I have ever had! For very decent price and they also serve delicious variations of rice! Wow! I cannot get over how amazing this place is. The staff is always so friendly with us and we come here so often. The ambiance is very cool and they serve Japanese beer! Do yourself a favor and come here.

We were in Chicago for my fiance's birthday and came across Friends Ramen. I was in HEAVEN!! The ramen was delicious, the location was great and the decor just made my soul happy. My wish for the wall was for them to make it out to San Francisco! The young man working solo front of house was over the moon when he heard about my wish because he had just visited San Fran two months prior and he couldn't stop raving about all his experiences. I walked out of there with a warm belly and smiling soul. Thank you.

This place is a transportation to another world, like a portal to delicious goodness in the middle of Chicago. The two servers that are here are the nicest and most friendly you could find in town. The woodwork and music create an environment that is unlike anywhere else I've ever been and I hope they stay open forever. Thanks again and don't ever change! Don't forget to make a wish on the wall!
Fantastic experience, nuff said, go

We live just around the corner and walked pass it everyday since it opened some years ago, just never really thought the food will be special, because it is like Ramen tapas.  For people who really enjoys Ramen this is a big no no.   But for the slightly more chic crowd, this goes along with the "less is more" idea. The place is tiny, about 8 tiny tables made of wood blocks, not mean for you to sit long and work on your paper, and for w small place, high turn over is important.  The food is actually good, everything we tried was quite impressive, but not "I will be back soon" good.  The broth base is the same, just adding a few twists to it.  The qty is tiny, about 2 full bites and it s gone.  It is surely good for snack.  A single bowl is about 1/4 of the real thing (don't let the broth fool you).  I personally prefer the Ramen at Misoya, it is original.  Did someone say Ramen-san?
Great selection of ramen and especially welcoming to find veg-friendly broth! Good size bowls that allow sampling the menu items.

I've eaten here three times and I'm writing a very fair review for this very expensive restaurant.   Let's explore portion size first.  The first visit I had no clue how tiny my $6 bowl of chicken ramen would be but it is a third or a quarter size of a traditional bowl served in other restaurants but I enjoyed the flavor and got a $3 melon soda so I spent $10 the first time and made note that the seated benches are tiny so it's not a comfortable sitting situation if you have back issues or you are taller than 5 feet 2 you are going to feel VERY UNCOMFORTABLE.   Second visit I tried a combo for $15 and I got 2 tiny soups a tiny gyoza dumpling and the server didn't charge me extra for me wanting to substitute out the coke products for a melon soda. I was happy with my second visit even though I hate the ugly and loud hip hop that plays here 24/7.  The server explained it's his music selection so I suggested other genres of music and he smiled and said he'd consider it.  Today was my 3rd and final visit.  Today I ordered a combination again, asked for a can of melon soda rather than a coke beverage, chose 2 tiny soups and a tiny hot rice and was charged $22.50 rather than the fixed combination rate of $15 because my waitress isn't fluent with English and didn't tell me there would be a price hike because I picked a different soup and the can of melon soda. The music continues to play loud and of course it's house music and hip hop.  This is my final visit because I'd rather spend $14 receiving a giant portion of well prepared traditional Japanese ramen than blow $22 in a loud restaurant with uncomfortable seating, and servers who can't understand you.  The music here is uninteresting, uninspiring and I actually asked a few other guests if they enjoyed the music and none of these guests spoke up but I'm here to say save your money and get the whole portion of ramen elsewhere and you'll leave satisfied and less broke.  I don't want to order ramen as an appetizer also the more shallow bowls don't retain the heat of the soup so it's half cold by the time you've eaten your half portion anyway!
I order eci Katsu rice and tan tan ramen  both are good !
Outstanding. Inexpensive, delicious, great service.

It’s Asian fusion, rather than real Japanese ramen.  A nice concept, but I was a bit underwhelmed as my expectation was higher.  Each bowl of ramen is so small, I would call it an appetizer.  If you are hungry, order a few items from the menu.

Cute idea with the small bowl, but not enough variety to execute the concept. The one bowl (Veggie Tan Men) I really wanted they no longer sale, but its still on their website. Overall it was tasty, but portions are way too small. All it did was frustrate and leave me desiring more. We finished lunch at another restaurant down the street.

Novelty concept noodle shop. All serving comes in a small portion costing $6. Typically one would need at least 2-3 servings.  The setting in cosy and intimate with friendly service.  Food is tasty but they really do not serve ramen. There is the egg noodles and rice noodles options but these are certainly not ramen. The rice dishes are OK too.

The ramen comes in only one size--a bowl only slightly bigger than a cup, for $6. The ramen itself (I ended up having 3 bowls) was quite tasty with a rich delicious broth, melt-in-your-mouth pork belly, and good noodles. The ramen was also more pan-Asian than Japanese in my opinion.  The setting was nice and the service was quick and pleasant. Normally I would give 4 stars for a place like this, but the small serving size really irked me. It is a good idea for people to try different kinds of ramen, but at least give an option for a regular-sized bowl.

My best friend and I spent 4 days in Chicago and this was by far my favorite place we ate at.  Our waiter was incredibly nice, the food was great and the atmosphere was very fun.  Also, the prices were really great.  If you’re in the area, you should definitely give it a try.
Awesome spot for ramen. Feels like you're in Japan. Good vibes, cool atmosphere, friendly service and delicious food!

Bowls are very very small, so they couldn't place enough noodles in bowl, but broths are super tasty!! Pork belly was just fat portion of it, so I didn't like that, but again flavors were delicious. I'd go back again and try other ones. Wish they had a large to enjoy more noodles!
Great food, cool little place, beautiful interior
Don't miss the "boss sauce" at this place!
It was just amazing on all levels
Interesting concept, but they should have the option to supersize the bowls :)
2 bowls make a hearty delicious meal. My favorite ramen spot in Chicago hands down
Food is mediocre, small portions. It's just ok, the waitress was nice, helpful and accommodating.
Great ramen joint with beautiful interiors.
Great food and cool music, but the portion sizes are unfortunately small.
Awesome concept.. Food is EXCELLENT.. Lol chairs and tables are heavy as hell and im a big guy!! Watch ur knees but the fiod is worth it!! :-)
Good food. Portions not too big, which I liked.

Amazing place! Perfect size ramen for me personally, didn't leave feeling bloated for once, takoyaki were perfect temp (for some reason I've only had overly hot takoyaki? idk if this is actually a plus but I enjoyed it) definitely coming back many times more to try everything, curious about the cheesy ramen. We had that top left one with the double name (broth was dope) and the karaage chicken one (less impressive but still dope)
Little gem. Loved it. Great food.

If you like the option to have many ramen choices and side dishes in one meal, thiz iz the place for you. For my wife, she can choose and control the amounts of food to intake in this restaurant depends on how hungry she is. The ramen comes in a very small portion and a normal guy needs 2 ramen at an average meal i think. You will end up walking out about $20 a person with drink. Dining choice and experience is decent, but there is alot of competitive choices in Chitown.

Customer service was bomb diggity, food was f***in good, just order 2 bowls and get that melon cream soda...I tell u what ( In my Hank Hill voice ) that cream soda was so God darn good, I ordered 3 of them 💯👌🏽
Cute ramen place with great efficient service. Id go back

I want to start by saying, I actually enjoyed the food. It didn't blow me away, but it was cozy and fast. But lets talk about my customer experience.  I walked up to the restaurant at around 9:40. I was just looking at the menu/seeing when they close when a young man came to the door to invite me and a friend in. We went in and sat immediately. I saw that they had been cleaning up and I felt bad about coming in, but thought if I was literally waved in, it wouldn't be a big deal.  Then, got the menu and the server gives me an incredibly rude "yeah so last call is in like 2 minutes..." and just stands there... alright I think, I can order fast, I know what I want. So I order what I wanted and the server sighs and says "that's it?" implying I should order more. Now, I get that I should make them making us food worthwhile, so I double up on the order ($33 of food). The waiter then asks about DRINKS. So I order 2 more drinks. At this point I've spent 10x what I expected but, whatever.  Food comes out and my friend and I literally scarf it down. Probably ate all of it in 4-5 minutes. I was trying to leave as soon as possible. We are paid and out by 9:56. It's not even 10 yet. Before we leave, the server asks "are you from Chicago?" in the most condescending manner I've ever heard. This is after I gave him a ~$10 tip on a ~$30 bill.  So overall, this is a restaurant I wouldn't recommend as the service simply doesn't understand hospitality. I was bummed because I liked the food, service was just god awful.
Excellent food. Great service. Thoroughly enjoyable. Cozy,this place proves that good things come in small packages.
Meat and egg were cold. Portion size was extremely small too.
Tried the spicy miso and kimchi bowls. Both were delicious.  Super friendly staff.
Overall 4.5 stars Environment 4.5 stars Staff 5 stars Food 4.5 stars Price $$/$$$$  Good for a small bite. But if you can eat a lot, this is not for you. Nice wood furnitures. Really small seats.
Great ramen!
The portions are small but fair for the $6 price tag on the bowl. The taste is pretty good.

I stopped here on a whim while shopping off Michigan Ave. I love trying new cuisines and have been hoping to try Ramen soon, as I love any and all Asian food. The place was small but had a really cool vibe, with wooden tables and chairs. The server immediately let me pick a spot and came by with the menu. I ordered one of the combos with gyozas, a salad, and ramen. Their ramen bowls are small, but the idea is to get something else or multiple ramen bowls, as their are very cheap ($6 a bowl). The combo was perfect and came out immediately. It was beyond delicious. I loved it and was so pleased to find a great hole in the wall place to eat.

My low key favorite Ramen spot. If I ever bring you here to eat, I really care about you. Softball sized bowls are their only size at around $6 each. They also sell beer, rice, and cream sodas. Come for the food and stay music!

This restaurant is small which sometimes means there is a wait, but it is well worth it. The ramen comes in smaller portions, so you can try more than one kind during a visit. A lot of people order 3 bowls at once. The ramen was delicious. This place is definitely on my list of places I would go back to when returning to Chicago.
The food is so good, the service was top notch, the ambiance is cozy, and I definitely plan to come back!
A cozy environment to enjoy spicy bowls of ramen with friends. Everything is so delicious. Staff are courteous and kind.
Awesome little Ramen shop for what it is. Mini ramen bowls with Prices to match, nice atmosphere, and great service. This is more of a lunch spot for me. Definitely on my list of regular Go-to's

This is perfect for a small bite. However if you want a full meal, might as well go to a place with a regular size bowl of ramen. The tonkostu base wasn't terrible. But for the amount of noodles and meat, you can get 4 times as much for double the price elsewhere. Otherwise, this is a great option for a snack.
I've been here twice. They serve small bowls of ramen for $6 a bowl. It's good. I enjoyed it. Next time I go I want to try their rice bowl.

A cozy ramen place. Party of more than 2-4 is not recommended as that will not be particularly comfortable. Servings are small so a minimum of 2 dish are required person and if you are very hungry you juat might go for more. However taste of the food is good enough for you to enjoy multiple dishes with a smile on your face. The price of each main dish is $5-6 so it will not break the bank to order multiple dishes. I would highly recommend the chicken dumplings, The Tan Tan Men and the Spicy Miso Ramen. Did not particularly enjoyed the Chicken Ramen. However by all means feel free to explore.

walked in and didn't realize you can have smaller bowls.  I got two plus an app and it was fantastic.   Ramen was cooled quicklyand very flavorful.  They had great variety too.  My wife who doesn't usually like ramen and she said it was good.  Edit: missed words
Portions are small but is delicious
Nice and cozy place and good food. Make sure to order multiple plates ;)

Ok so ramen. I don't really have a good introduction to Ramen (except the kind that comes in a cup and on a supermarket shelf). So this place was my test run and I can say I was not disappointed:  1. The appetizers were excellent -- the chicken dumplings tasty and sweet, the fried chicken addictively and delicious  2. I went for the veg Tai Men? Ramen and it was pretty great. My friends ordered different kinds and used a generous helping of chili sauce to account for taste  3. The prices are excellent  4. The bathroom view (it's a one way mirror from the inside and umm it gave me a lot of anxiety and I'm not sure the world needs that sort of novelty. At all)  5. The service, simple, no fuss and very helpful  A few things to keep in mind:  1. No reservations 2. Limited space and really not for large groups, our party of 4 was at a table which faced the main door and each time it opened the lovely Chicago winter air hit us hard (we had to move and squeeze in a 2 person booth, something our server tried to stop us from) 3. Realllyyyyy limited alcohol selection (so do the boozing before or after)  All in all, highly recommend and will return
Meh
It’s tapas style ramen. We had 3 different bowls and the crab ramen was our favourite. Good service and cute setting.
Amazing ramen, great prices, and a really nice vibe.

Small, cozy with wooden chairs and furniture through the whole place.   You get a cup of ramen and can keep refilling it as much as you want for another serving. People are friendly, only wish is that it was open later.  It's great, and also really good 1-4 AM coming home late night food.
Disappointing: it is all too small. Menu and portions-bowl.
Super cool looking place. The portions are small and cheap so you can order several items.   Great service
Small portions, made to share with friends. Ramen is delicious!
Nice sized portions so you can try several varieties. Priced well. Bench tables are not comfortable, but the service is fast so you don't sit very long.
Cool vibe in this small ramen spot. Portions are small so you can try more then one bowl. Everything I tried was really good. Wish they had an option for a larger size.
Small dining room, good service and food

Don't expect to be full from one bowl. I got the karaage chicken and tan tan men. Both of which were delicious but serving sizes are really small. Pricey for what it is, but that being said, it's still delicious. Broth is lacking a bit but chicken was amazing. Atmosphere is nice and cozy but the chairs were a bit uncomfortable.
VERY BEST RAMEN!!  tapas style!

Okay. The restaurant looked cool. I lived in Japan for many years in the place fit right in. Now let's talk about the ramen. $6 for a cup of ramen that you can make it home by using cup noodle and a few over the counter ingredients the broth had no soul it lacked love. I would not recommend this place for any true Ramen lovers you will be disappointed. They only serve a miso base which technically seems like they just use a squeeze tube of miso and some hot water boil some noodles and throw in some ingredients. Now if you know anything about Ramen that should be enough good luck and happy eating
nice and cozy place, bowls are bit small, little bit expensive
Great.
Get 2 bowls and enjoy. I love the hot oil, but you have to love spice. Just a great find and fairly inexpensive

One and only Ramen Tasting in Chicago that is budget-friendly.  Quick $6 Ramen is a light satisfactory meal in 6 mins.  PERFECT portion and taste with blend of ingredients.  For a change, its limited carbs... where did the Ramen go?  😁
Small bowl for Japanese style food. And it is small bowl for sure. The ramen bowl is 6 dollars but you will need 2-3bowls for an adult man. The pork rice is really good.

The food was alright, but service was the slowest I've had at any ramen spot I've been to. It was over 10 minutes before we received our drinks and around 30-40 before we received our food at 3pm on a Sunday.
Small but delicious portions
Very good food !!! Me and my husband really love this place !!!!
Really fantastic broth, but the effect is spoiled somewhat by the fact that they use spaghetti noodles instead of ramen. :/

Fun, small ramen shop with interesting mini bowl concept. While almost every other ramen shop you pick a type of ramen and they give you a big bowl of it, here you pick a couple smaller bowls ($6 ea) and you're able to try a variety of ramen flavors instead of one. Spicy miso ramen is a must try. It is also a small place and seats are very tight so try to go early or on a weeknight.
Good concept. Ramen is good

The portions are small, not filling and not worth the price. Imagine buying store bought ramen for restaurant prices. We sat at the bar-like area and the seats were small and heavy. If you go despite my warning then get ready to put some muscle into pulling those chairs out. The sitting arrangements are also to tight. This is what we bought:  Coke: 2.00 Gyoza (5): 5.00 Chicken Ramen: 6.00 Pork Belly Bowl: 6.00 Total: 19.00 + taxes  I gave this place 2 stars because the food wasn't bad but we still had to go to another restaurant once we left.

Friends sushi on Rush has always been more edgy and unique than most sushi places around this neighborhood . Finally they open new ramen than just the boring bowl of noodles. Upon entering, I feel that every turn I am entering an old manor Japanese home with century old decor, entirely new experience. We were welcoming server who, from the moment we sat down until the very last moment we left, couldn't have been more attentive and professional. The menu’s flavors have likewise expanded, reaching from the early classic miso style to the today techniques. Friends ramen was truly made for all drinkers. Wide ranging of sake list and Japanese draft that will appeal to every palate.

Awesome atmosphere, which was small and cozy.  Food was decent, but concept of tapas style ramen was real cool. Overall good experience, but food wasn't anything special in regards to the flavors. I did enjoy the spicy miso ramen.

A little on the pricey side as the bowls are very small and you'll want to order two or three to be satisfied. The seats there are *very* uncomfortable, but the food is great! I've never been disappointed with my meal.
It's small but the food is good

Pretty atrocious. Noodles were over-cooked spaghetti, the gyoza was obviously frozen, the broth was watery and bland, and the check was 17 for small bowls of bad food. The service was awkward too. They gave me my dishes then came back and …

(Translated by Google) Recommended for those who are small. I think this size is good for those who have eaten a lot of food in Chicago. Ramen is good, but mini meat bowl is recommended. If you're hungry, it's best to ask for two.  (Original) 小食な方におすすめ。シカゴで大量の食事でぐったりしてしまったかたにはこのサイズはいいと思う。ラーメンもいいが、ミニ肉丼がおすすめ。空腹なときは2つ頼むのがよい。
Small portions, but the taste is excellent

I LOVED this place!! First, I love the concept that the portions are small so you can try more than one! Second, both of the ones I ordered were so yummy.  I got the spicy veggie ramen with tofu which had a fabulous flavor and was sufficiently hot when it arrived. I also ordered the crab ramen with ginger, kale and bean spouts. It was fabulous. The chili sauce on the table kicked up the broth (after I'd fished all the nibbly bits out) for a great finish. The service was fast and helpful! Perfect for lunch.
(Translated by Google) Delicious hot food, recommended combos.  (Original) Deliciosa comida caliente, recomendables los combos.

Pretty cool spot right off of the Chicago red line station. Ordered a bowl of ramen and one of chicken and rice. Both were not hot, just warm? Flavors/taste was underwhelming and did not really stand out. The sever was super friendly and welcoming, though.
Great food, amazing atmosphere. Our waiter was really helpful. Food was hot.
Loved the food, the ambience
The portion sizes are small, but the tastiness of the dishes is wonderful. it's a small cozy spot, ideal for one on one talks.
Amazing ramen and the staff are excellent and polite
Small portions , good taste, friendly server
This place is unbelievable, my favorite ramen ever. Just stumbled on it and was blown away. Small cheap portions encourage ordering 2-3 ramen, do it!
Awesome place, the small bowls are great so that you can try different kinds of ramen in one sitting.
Good soup but the portions are kids size
It's a little bit on the pricey side, but I like the idea of having different bowls on the same time. Overall the food tastes great.

My new favorite Ramen spot in Chicago.  Unlike other places they serve mini ramen bowls here so expect to order 2 per person. My favorite was the Tan Tan.  The Karaage and Yam appetizers were also very tasty.  If you have room at the end the crepe cakes are also a must, great light sweet way to end the meal.  The ramen was perfectly hot as it's made to order so not sure why others thought they were warm.  Pro tips: get extra lettuce with the Karaage appetizer and an extra side of the spicy mayo no matter what you order as it's great to dip anything in.

Amazing place with incredible aesthetics inside and out. Friendly and very personal staff willing to guide you through an unforgettable ramen experience. Chili sauce is a must try on the spicy pork belly for any heat lovers.
amazing, flavorful vegetarian/vegan options.
(Translated by Google) I like his Japanese food, his beer and his wooden place !!!!  (Original) Me gusta su comida japonesa,su cerveza y su local de madera!!!!

I'm a fan of spicy food and LOVED the hot chili sauce they have on the tables to be added to the soup. The small portions are fun to eat. Sadly, I tried 3 different bowls and thought all 3 were just okay. None of the soups were served hot, just warm at best.
Great spicy Miso ramen at an affordable price.  It's a pretty unassuming place, but cozy and delicious.
Good food great for dates only  thing I would change is the napkins
Their ramen is fantastic but portion sizes are  intended to be small and as a result more expensive.

The wife's and my favorite new little spot to hit up! We stumbled into Friends Ramen after a long walk and had three of the ramen that our server recommended. They were all very tasty and more than enough - we could have had just two but we wanted the Chicken Karaage again!  The place is pretty small and the tables are definitely cozy.  There aren't more than maybe 7-8 tables there and the bathroom has see through glass.  We will definitely be back again and again!
Love the small plate style Ramen and apps here. Allows you to try a couple of things.

Great food! I love the variety of choices of ramen dishes, as well as the small bowl size and low price per bowl, which allows you to try lots of different kinds of ramen. The only thing I would change would be the loud music choices (I don't really care for '90s rap, especially on full blast). It kind of made it hard to concentrate on the food and conversation I was trying to have at my table.

The vibe here is very cozy, very homey and warm. It's a small little spot. The idea here is tapas style dim-sum like ramen. Everything I had was delicious, and the service was friendly. I tried about half the menu, loved the crab ramen, crunchy shrimp, and pork belly and rice especially. All very reasonable pricing, especially for a trendy near North location. Ate like kings for 2, total came to just under $60. New favorite local ramen spot!
I lived in Japan for a number of years. Reminded me of the ramen across the pond.
Great atmosphere and even better ramen. The portions are small so you can try there many different varieties.
Best ramen ever ! Small quantity but small prices so you can try different thing on the menu. Add to that cool staff and fast service. We will come again and try the rest of the menu !
Delicious food in smaller servings

Ambiance was nice, the food looked good. Unfortunately all of their menu has pork & chicken broth mixed together-- no options for people who don't eat pork. Anyway, I ordered the two veggie ramen and got chicken on them. The spicy one was …
Best Ramen in Chicago
Good ramen,  small portions but it's not without its advantages.   Moses the server was great.  Nice ambiance,  good music overall a great experience.
Ramen was good, not the best in Chicago. The idea of small portions so you can taste them all still doesn't get to me but it was good. Not as awesome as Friends Sushi.
